TITLE: Adding a macro method to Request class
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to extend the Request class with a 'wantsJSON' method for checking if the request accepts JSON responses. The method examines the request's content type headers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adonisjs/v6-docs/blob/main/content/docs/concepts/extending_the_framework.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// title: src/extensions.ts
import { Request } from '@adonisjs/core/http'

Request.macro('wantsJSON', function (this: Request) {
  const firstType = this.types()[0]
  if (!firstType) {
    return false
  }

  return firstType.includes('/json') || firstType.includes('+json')
})
```

