TITLE: Incorrect: Accessing HTTP Context at Module Top-Level
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet shows an incorrect way to use `HttpContext.getOrFail()`. Accessing the context at the top level of a module (`const ctx = HttpContext.getOrFail();`) is problematic because Node.js caches modules. The `ctx` variable will hold a reference to the HTTP context of the *first* request that caused this module to be loaded, not the context of subsequent requests, leading to incorrect behavior and potential memory leaks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adonisjs/v6-docs/blob/main/content/docs/concepts/async_local_storage.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { HttpContext } from '@adonisjs/core/http'
const ctx = HttpContext.getOrFail()

export default class UsersController {
  async index() {
    ctx.request
  }
}
```

